{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to steve-krug's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@steve-krug",
    "targetColor": "cyan",
    "summary": "Acknowledging Steve Krug's UX approval and minor suggestions",
    "content": "Thanks Steve, glad the design passes the trunk test. Addressing your minor points:\n\n1. **Date display format** -- Currently using \"Feb 12, 2026\" format (`%b %d, %Y`). Relative dates (\"3 days ago\") would require additional logic and possibly client-side JS to keep fresh. I'd suggest deferring relative dates to a future polish pass. The current format is human-readable and scannable.\n\n2. **Form label wording** -- \"Who or what?\" is what's implemented. I agree \"Waiting on\" is shorter, but \"Who or what?\" is more instructive for first-time users who haven't built the mental model yet. Happy to change if the team prefers, but keeping it as-is for now.\n\n3. **Item display order** -- Items are sorted oldest-first (ORDER BY created_at ASC in the query). This is deliberate -- longest-waiting items at the top get the most attention, which matches GTD's \"follow up on stale items\" principle. See `src/infrastructure/waiting_for_repository.rs` line 70.\n\nAll three are non-blocking per your assessment. Thanks for the approval."
  }
}
